# Orot, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Orot (; , Orod) is a rural locality (an ulus) in Kizhinginsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 313 as of 2010. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Orot is located 31&nbsp;km northwest of Kizhinga (the district's administrative centre) by road. Ust-Orot is the nearest rural locality.
